      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">fronglo wrote:</div><div class="orig">So now we can't join a 10 man AND a 25 man in the same week?  Don't like that at all.  Means less emblems and loot.</div></div> <br />There should be no need.  If you're progressing reasonably in a raid of either size, you'll cap out on your points for the week (probably with no further need to do retro heroics).  Bosses will drop the exact same ilvl in 10 and 25, so no benefit from jumping to 25 for higher-level gear (i.e. &quot;strict 10 man&quot; raiding is going away as a category, because everyone will be strict, even if they moonlight in 25s for a week or 2). <br /> <br />What you won't be <s>forced</s>able to do anymore is slum in 10-mans to supplement the 25-man loot table in order to gear faster.  However, everyone will be in the same boat, so it won't affect the progression race.  And it might help slow down the onset of burnout.  The ability to do so in the first place was a side effect of the LK raid structure, and it's pretty clear from the changes that it's one that wasn't fully intended.</div>
      <div class="msgFtFrame"><div class="msgFtFrameFix"></div><div class="msgReplies"><a href="javascript:scrollTo(0,0);">&#9650; Page top</a> |   <a href="/forum.html?forum=21&amp;mid=128595245894381042&amp;page=1&amp;howmany=50#msg1285955217242998996" class="icon-linktothis" rel="nofollow">Link to this post</a>  </div></div>
