      <div class="msgContentFrame">I kept track of it until the thing about heroics. That part got really confusing. It sounds like it means that if I have 25 people raiding 10-mans, I need to kill the LK on normal with every possible combination of 10-man groups (Which means 25 X 24 X 23 X 22 .....) before I could actually try heroic bosses with all players in my guild. This can't be right, as you'd need years of raiding to get that done - hence why it confuses me. <br /> <br />Also, I don't understand how the 'lock out' system really works. If I did not kill Putricide yet, and I join a group of 9 people who have killed him, will he get marked as killed in my list?  <br /> <br />And what about this: I have completed the Valithria encounter, but nothing else post-Saurfang yet. I join a group who has cleared Blood wing, but has Plague and Frost wing to go. What happens? I'd like to be able to do the Plague Wing with them as we both still need that, but will that even be possible? Will I get Blood Wing marked off on my list and will the other nine people get Valithria marked off on their lists?<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">&quot;My guildy Kasdaye&quot; wrote:</div><div class="orig">Gearscore for raiders is like Goldshire for roleplayers.</div></div></div></div>
