      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Borsuk wrote:</div><div class="orig">I realize that you generally need more than 1 day to do a raid, but I don't see why it needs to be a week.  Why can't you just reset raids every 3 or so days if you so choose.</div></div> <br />Because if it takes you 2-3 days to clear a raid you'd have to raid every day in order to clear it before the reset. Having a full week gives people the freedom to raid only a few times a week, on whichever days they choose. It also lets Blizz limit the amount of raid drops too keep people from gearing (and burning out on the raid) up twice and fast. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Borsuk wrote:</div><div class="orig">But for people like me, who might hit 1/3 of the raid per week - having the option to reset would get me into a lot more raids...</div></div> <br />That's part of what this new system is supposed to fix. If that ICC pug only goes 4/12 you can now join another pug (so long as they're also at least 4/12) instead of being stuck for the rest of the week.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>75 Rabbit/75 Sheep/75 Coeurl/75 Eft/75 Raptor/75 Hippogryph/75 Puk <br />75 Scorpion/75 Wamoura/75 Pixie/75 Peiste/64 Sabotender <br />51 Bird/41 Mandragora/40 Bee/37 Crawler/37 Bat <br /> <br />Items no one cares about: O <br />Missions no one cares about: O <br />Crafts no one cares about: O</div></div>
