      <div class="msgContentFrame">There's been a lot of discussion about this topic and the more I think about it, the less I like it. <br /> <br />PUGs will be beyond chaotic. Nearly every PUG has people who drop out mid-raid. Replacing these slots will be a nightmare for raid leaders. &quot;Let me see what you've cleared....&quot; With more chaos in organization, I'm guessing most PUG leaders will just abandon leading PUGs at all. Leaving casual raiders and raiding alts with fewer options. <br /> <br />Progression groups will have to commit to a progression schedule more completely than we thought. Let's face it, most organized raid guilds do this more or less already. But the promises of being able to swap down to 10mans when needed is useless to hardmode/heroic groups, which is what progression raids are doing. Normal mode is for gearing, hardmode is where progression raiders live. <br /> <br />So really, the only group to seriously benefit from the new lockout system will be normal mode, organized, regular groups. Maybe that's the majority of raids out there and maybe that's a great thing. But right now it seems actually even more convoluted than before. <br /> <br />On the other hand, I could be way off. Until we see the system in place and watch trade chat it's hard to say exactly how it will play out. But right now, it seems very &quot;meh.&quot;<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm">&quot;I'm gonna need to see more math I don't understand to believe all this&quot; <br />日本人彼女募集中 <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Zede" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Zede">Zede the Undying</a> • <a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Phezz" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Phezz">Phezz, the Insane Kingslayer</a> • <a href="HTTP://