      <div class="msgContentFrame">Personally speaking, I'm a little less than thrilled with the idea of the flexible raid lockout.  It'd be one thing if we did, in fact, get it introduced with Cataclysm, when all loot and achievements will be considered more or less equal across 10 and 25 man raids, and quite another when there are still some people who have a few achievements left to finish up that, for one reason or another, are not feasible for them at this time on 25.  I'm in probably a slightly better than average guild right now.  We clear 9/12 heroics weekly on 25, but heroic Putricide and Sindragosa haven't yet fallen.  Not bad, I don't think, but not top end.  I can accept that, fine.  However, my 10 man has been scraping closer and closer to a heroic Lich King kill.  With the advent of the 'flexible' raid lockout, I worry that those of us who would just like to finish one last achievement on 10 man are, to put it bluntly, screwed, assuming we have 25 man commitments as well.  Oh well.  Time to push the 10 man to finish off old Arthas before 4.0.1 hits, I suppose.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Alleria&amp;cn=Celosia" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Alleria&amp;cn=Celosia">Celosia</a> All Holy, All The Time</div></div>
